hopobject.body: What sort of music do you listen to? manforce condom pics This is all to highlight the fact that over the last two or three years – this generation has been a long one, and the battle won early – FIFA hasn't had a great deal to shoot for. As objectives go, FIFA's generation-opening gambit of “Take on a seemingly invincible foe and become the best football game in the world!” has a rousing quality that “Stay good” struggles to match. The result has been a series apparently shy of tinkering too intimately with the essential moving parts of its gameplay – no amount of capitalised marketing neologisms can hide the lack of significant development in FIFA's football over the last few years.
